  <span id="freeText6909182473923554447" style="display:none">My first misfire since I came home in November.<br /><br />Huge run on sentences, extensive description, and I'm outta here.<br /><br />There are only two humans on earth who should be able to bend the rules of the English language to tell their story: Cormac McCarthy and James Ellroy. I realize Doctorow came well before these authors, so I can understand why some people may have a soft spot for him. Not me.<br /><br />This same plotline of boy meets mafia was done much better in Nicholas Pileggi's Wiseguy, which later became the basis for the movie Goodfellas. Stick to that one.</span>
