<div id="review_2715257780" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2715257780" />
    <a title="Christopher Saunders" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13546014-christopher-saunders"><img alt="Christopher Saunders" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612565718p2/13546014.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2715257780?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christopher Saunders" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christopher Saunders" href="/user/show/13546014-christopher-saunders">Christopher Saunders</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812981179" href="/book/show/7845345-billy-bathgate">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=2019-reads">2019-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=friday-night-reads">friday-night-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=2020-reads">2020-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2715257780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3377048921974043920">Historical novel about a teenager growing up in the 1930s Bronx who falls in with notorious gangster Dutch Schultz and becomes a gofer, confidante and right-hand man as Federal investigators and rival criminals close in. Typical of Doctorow, it’s a sprawling, somewhat unfocused yet compulsively engaging work of historical fiction, filled with colorful vignettes and larger-than-life characters. The novel flits between Billy’s gangland exploits, his picturesque romance with Schultz’s moll Drew, hi</span>
  <span id="freeText3377048921974043920" style="display:none">Historical novel about a teenager growing up in the 1930s Bronx who falls in with notorious gangster Dutch Schultz and becomes a gofer, confidante and right-hand man as Federal investigators and rival criminals close in. Typical of Doctorow, it’s a sprawling, somewhat unfocused yet compulsively engaging work of historical fiction, filled with colorful vignettes and larger-than-life characters. The novel flits between Billy’s gangland exploits, his picturesque romance with Schultz’s moll Drew, his efforts to transcend and honor his background, and to stay alive as his mentor grows increasingly desperate and violent, culminating in an ill-fated plot to assassinate Thomas Dewey, the New York State Prosecutor. The book’s greatness is somewhat qualified by Doctorow’s penchant for grandiloquent run-on sentences, which becomes irritating at times when the story could use a more straightforward approach (the contrast between the protagonist’s rambling and the terse gangster’s dialogue is jarring; I assume by design, but not satisfying either way). But it’s memorable for the vivid collage of life during Prohibition and the Depression, a combination character study and gangster story that transcends its shortcomings. Made into a film with Dustin Hoffman, Bruce Willis and Nicole Kidman in 1991.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3377048921974043920" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


